article.description: Joel Bolomboy scored 20 points and grabbed 13 rebounds -- his seventh double-double in as many games this season -- helping Weber State to a 95-57 victory over NAIA Pacific Union on Tuesday night
article.headline: Bolomboy notches 7th double-double, Weber State wins 95-57
article.linkText: Bolomboy notches 7th double-double, Weber State wins 95-57
article.story: OGDEN, Utah -- Joel Bolomboy scored 20 points and grabbed 13 rebounds -- his seventh double-double in as many games this season -- helping Weber State to a 95-57 victory over NAIA Pacific Union on Tuesday night. Zach Braxton scored the first six points for Weber State (5-2), which won the Gulf Coast Showcase in Florida last week and ran its win streak to five games. Braxton finished with 15 points on 6-for-9 shooting from the floor. McKay Cannon and Kyndahl Hill scored 10 points each for Weber. Jarron Crump scored 23 points, including a trio of 3-pointers, and Mike Hill added 11 for Pacific Union, which briefly took a 3-2 lead on a Crump 3-pointer only to see the Wildcats go off on a 23-4 run. Bolomboy capped the run with back-to-back dunks. He entered the game leading the country in double-doubles with six. Weber had a 56-16 edge in points in the paint.
